just_use enumerator.py

# label: WORKHORSE + INTRICATE
# role: BFS move generator + focus rule + doomed-third filter

The Python equivalent of `Game.Agent.Enumerator.elm`. Owns
the move generator that drives every BFS expansion, plus
all the helpers that tune what gets yielded: the doomed-
third filter, the extractable index (loop inversion), and
the focus rule + lineage tracking.

## Status

- **Mirrors:** `games/lynrummy/elm/src/Game/Agent/Enumerator.elm`.
- **Origin:** lifted from `bfs_solver.py` 2026-04-26 as the
  module split landed.

## Move types

Five move types, each must touch a TROUBLE card or a
GROWING build:

- **(a) ExtractAbsorb** — peel/pluck/yank/steal/split_out a
  card from HELPER and absorb it onto a TROUBLE / GROWING
  target.
- **(a') FreePull** — TROUBLE singleton absorbs onto target.
- **(b) Push** — TROUBLE 1- or 2-partial pushes onto HELPER
  so the helper grows.
- **(b') Engulf** — GROWING 2-partial swallows a HELPER
  stack into a single legal stack that graduates to
  COMPLETE. Reuses the `push` desc shape.
- **(c) Splice** — TROUBLE singleton inserts into a HELPER
  pure/rb run length 4+, splitting it cleanly.
- **(d) Shift** — peel a HELPER donor card to replace the
  stolen end of a length-3 run. No spawn.

## Doomed-third filter (OPTIMIZE_PYTHON)

- `completion_inventory(helper, trouble)` — `set` of
  shape keys available as candidate "third cards":
  helper cards + trouble singletons.
- `completion_shapes(partial)` — shapes that would extend
  a length-2 partial into a legal length-3 stack.
- `has_doomed_third(partial, inventory)` — true iff no
  completion candidate exists.
- `admissible_partial(merged, inventory)` — combined gate
  used at every absorb site. Skips moves that produce
  dead-end partials.
- State-level guard at the top of `enumerate_moves`:
  short-circuits to no-yield when any growing 2-partial
  has lost all its candidates.

## Extractable index (loop inversion)

`extractable_index(helper)` — built once per state. Maps
shape key → list of `(hi, ci, verb)`. The absorb loop
iterates the absorber's neighbor shapes and looks up
matching helper positions in O(1) per shape. Shift's donor
lookup also reads this index (filtered to peels) — same
shape as Elm's loop-inversion port.

## Focus rule + lineage

- `initial_lineage(trouble, growing)` — trouble entries in
  board order followed by pre-existing growing 2-partials.
- `move_touches_focus(desc, focus)` — true iff the move
  grows or consumes `focus`.
- `update_lineage(lineage, desc)` — advance the queue
  after a move.
- `enumerate_focused(state)` — wraps `enumerate_moves`
  with the focus filter + lineage update. The BFS engine
  calls this, not `enumerate_moves`, when the focus rule
  is on.
- `FOCUS_ENABLED` (module flag) — analysis tooling toggles
  this off to compare unrestricted vs focused plans.

## Pointers

- Elm sibling: `games/lynrummy/elm/src/Game/Agent/Enumerator.elm`.
- Python sibling: `bfs.py` (the engine that consumes
  `enumerate_focused`).
